2026-03-07T22:32:25.586464Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019cca6d-4992-7651-9f0a-5f10fb9bd6c2}:submission_dispatch{submission.id="019cca6d-58db-7a60-aacb-e26423c6c78a"}:turn{otel.name="session_task.turn" thread.id=019cca6d-4992-7651-9f0a-5f10fb9bd6c2 turn.id=019cca6d-58db-7a60-aacb-e26423c6c78a model=gpt-5.3-codex}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cd /home/m_srnic/ece493/group_project/ECE493Group19 && cat > /home/m_srnic/ece493/group_project/ECE493Group19/specs/001-user-login/checklists/auth.md <<'EOF'\n# Authentication Requirements Quality Checklist: User Login Authentication\n\n**Purpose**: Validate that login/authentication requirements are complete, clear, consistent, measurable, and scenario-complete before implementation/review.\n**Created**: 2026-03-07\n**Feature**: [/home/m_srnic/ece493/group_project/ECE493Group19/specs/001-user-login/spec.md](/home/m_srnic/ece493/group_project/ECE493Group19/specs/001-user-login/spec.md)\n\n**Note**: This checklist evaluates requirement quality, not implementation behavior.\n\n## Requirement Completeness\n\n- [ ] CHK001 Are input requirements fully specified for account identifier formats (username vs email rules, normalization, allowed characters, and length limits)? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-002, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK002 Are requirements defined for blank/whitespace-only credential submissions, including expected user-facing guidance? [Completeness, Spec В§Edge Cases]\n- [ ] CHK003 Are session lifecycle requirements documented beyond creation (timeout duration, renewal rules, and explicit invalidation/logout expectations)? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-004, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK004 Are locked-account and disabled-account guidance requirements specific enough to define required support contact content and channel format? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-009, Assumption]\n- [ ] CHK005 Are requirements defined for failure-event record retention, audit fields, and access controls for login-failure logs? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-011, Gap]\n\n## Requirement Clarity\n\n- [ ] CHK006 Is вЂњconfigured failure thresholdвЂќ unambiguous now that the threshold is fixed at 5 attempts/15 minutes? [Clarity, Conflict, Spec В§FR-007]\n- [ ] CHK007 Is вЂњactive accountвЂќ explicitly defined with a complete state model and authoritative source for status transitions? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-004, Assumption]\n- [ ] CHK008 Is вЂњnext-step guidanceвЂќ quantified with minimum required message elements so wording quality can be objectively reviewed? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-009, Ambiguity]\n- [ ] CHK009 Is вЂњAuthentication Service unavailableвЂќ clearly scoped to concrete failure classes (timeout, dependency error, partial response, upstream 5xx)? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-010, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK010 Is вЂњnormal operating conditionsвЂќ for SC-001 defined with explicit environmental assumptions and load profile boundaries? [Clarity, Spec В§SC-001, Ambiguity]\n\n## Requirement Consistency\n\n- [ ] CHK011 Do lockout requirements remain internally consistent across duplicate FR identifiers and narrative scenarios? [Consistency, Conflict, Spec В§FR-007]\n- [ ] CHK012 Are scenario statements and functional requirements aligned on when lockout is enforced (at threshold hit vs subsequent attempt)? [Consistency, Spec В§Edge Cases, Spec В§FR-007]\n- [ ] CHK013 Are retry requirements consistent with lockout/disabled restrictions so no contradictory recovery path is implied? [Consistency, Spec В§FR-006, Spec В§FR-008, Spec В§FR-009]\n- [ ] CHK014 Do traceability constraints (FR-012/FR-013) align with delivery workflow requirements in plan artifacts without conflict? [Consistency, Spec В§FR-012, Spec В§FR-013, Plan В§Constitution Check]\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Quality\n\n- [ ] CHK015 Are success criteria mapped one-to-one to functional requirements with explicit measurement method and data source? [Acceptance Criteria, Traceability, Spec В§SC-001..SC-005, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK016 Is SC-001 measurable with an exact timing boundary definition (start/end timestamps and dashboard-ready condition)? [Measurability, Spec В§SC-001]\n- [ ] CHK017 Is SC-005 (вЂњfirst attemptвЂќ completion) controlled for participant profile and test conditions to avoid ambiguous interpretation? [Measurability, Spec В§SC-005, Ambiguity]\n\n## Scenario Coverage\n\n- [ ] CHK018 Are primary, alternate, exception, and recovery flows all explicitly documented with requirement-level outcomes and boundaries? [Coverage, Spec В§User Scenarios, Spec В§Edge Cases]\n- [ ] CHK019 Are requirements defined for post-lockout recovery, including counter reset conditions and behavior immediately after lock expiry? [Coverage, Recovery Flow, Spec В§Edge Cases, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK020 Are requirements complete for already-authenticated users visiting login, including redirect behavior and loop-prevention constraints? [Coverage, Spec В§User Story 1 Scenario 2]\n- [ ] CHK021 Are dependency-failure scenarios defined for partial/intermittent Authentication Service degradation, not only full outage? [Coverage, Exception Flow, Spec В§FR-010, Gap]\n\n## Edge Case Coverage\n\n- [ ] CHK022 Are boundary conditions specified for exactly 5th failed attempt handling and atomicity under concurrent attempts? [Edge Case, Spec В§FR-007, Spec В§Edge Cases, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK023 Are requirements documented for mixed identifier collisions (email-like usernames, case sensitivity differences) to prevent inconsistent credential matching rules? [Edge Case, Spec В§FR-002, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK024 Are requirements specified for repeated retries during active lock windows to ensure consistent messaging and telemetry semantics? [Edge Case, Spec В§FR-008, Spec В§FR-011]\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n\n- [ ] CHK025 Are security requirements defined for session cookie properties (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite) and session fixation prevention? [Non-Functional, Security, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK026 Are accessibility requirements specified for login and error messaging (keyboard flow, focus order, screen-reader announcements)? [Non-Functional, Accessibility, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK027 Are reliability requirements defined for failure logging durability during dependency outages? [Non-Functional, Reliability, Spec В§FR-011, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK028 Are observability requirements specified with measurable alert thresholds for lockout spikes and authentication dependency failures? [Non-Functional, Operability, Gap]\n\n## Dependencies & Assumptions\n\n- [ ] CHK029 Are external dependency expectations for the Authentication Service formally specified (SLA, timeout budget, error contract ownership)? [Dependency, Spec В§Assumptions & Dependencies, Gap]\n- [ ] CHK030 Is the assumption that dashboard availability is immediate translated into explicit dependency requirements and fallback behavior? [Assumption, Spec В§Assumptions & Dependencies, Gap]\n\n## Ambiguities & Conflicts\n\n- [ ] CHK031 Is duplicate numbering of FR-007 resolved to a single canonical requirement ID to preserve traceability integrity? [Ambiguity, Conflict, Spec В§FR-007]\n- [ ] CHK032 Is a stable requirement/acceptance ID linkage scheme defined to support FR-012 traceability audits across spec, plan, and tests? [Traceability, Spec В§FR-012, Gap]\nEOF","max_output_tokens":2000} thread_id=019cca6d-4992-7651-9f0a-5f10fb9bd6c2
