+- **FR-001**: The system MUST allow an authenticated student to open a schedule constraints editor for an available registration term.
+- **FR-002**: The system MUST allow a student to create, edit, and save custom schedule constraints that include time-based availability rules and course-selection preferences relevant to schedule generation.
+- **FR-003**: The system MUST validate each constraint before saving and reject any definition that is incomplete, malformed, or outside the allowed term context.
+- **FR-004**: When a save is rejected, the system MUST identify the specific constraint entries that need correction and preserve the student's unsaved edits for revision.
+- **FR-005**: When the submitted constraints conflict with each other, the system MUST warn the student about the conflict and allow the student to revise the constraints before finalizing the saved set.
+- **FR-006**: The system MUST store the saved constraint set so it is available to later schedule generation for the same student and term.
+- **FR-007**: The system MUST allow a student to delete any existing saved constraint and ensure deleted constraints are no longer applied to future schedule generation.
+- **FR-008**: If the system cannot save a submitted constraint set, it MUST report the failure and leave the previously saved constraint set unchanged.
+- **FR-009**: The system MUST limit changes made by this feature to the authenticated student's own constraint set for the selected term.
