+# Priorities Requirements Checklist: UC-27 Set Constraint Priorities
+
+**Purpose**: Validate the quality, clarity, and completeness of the constraint-priority requirements before implementation and review
+**Created**: 2026-03-11
+**Feature**: [spec.md](/home/thaia/ECE493Group19/specs/027-branch-constraint-priorities/spec.md)
+
+**Note**: This checklist is generated by the `/speckit.checklist` command based on feature context and requirements.
+
+## Requirement Completeness
+
+- [ ] CHK001 Are the eligible constraints for priority assignment explicitly defined, including whether all saved constraint types can be prioritized? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-001, Spec В§FR-010]
+- [ ] CHK002 Are the requirements explicit about whether every eligible constraint must receive a priority or whether documented defaults are permitted for unranked constraints? [Clarity, Spec В§Edge Cases, Spec В§FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK003 Are the save and replace semantics for the full priority set fully defined for create, update, and re-save scenarios? [Completeness, Spec В§User Story 1, Spec В§FR-004]
+- [ ] CHK004 Are the requirements complete for what happens to saved priorities when their referenced constraints are deleted, hidden, or otherwise unavailable? [Completeness, Spec В§Edge Cases, Spec В§FR-012]
+
+## Requirement Clarity
+
+- [ ] CHK005 Is the 1-to-5 scale defined unambiguously, including whether lower numbers always mean higher priority in every ranking context? [Clarity, Spec В§Clarifications, Spec В§FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK006 Is "displayed constraint order" precise enough to determine which order governs tie-breaking after sorting, filtering, or editing the editor view? [Ambiguity, Spec В§FR-008, Spec В§Tie-Breaking Rule]
+- [ ] CHK007 Is "outside the selected term" defined clearly enough to distinguish wrong-term references from deleted or stale constraints? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-005, Spec В§FR-012]
+- [ ] CHK008 Is "visible explanation" specific enough to evaluate message quality consistently across invalid-value and save-failure scenarios? [Measurability, Spec В§NFR-002, Spec В§SC-002]
+
+## Requirement Consistency
+
+- [ ] CHK009 Are the priority-model requirements consistent between the clarification note, user stories, functional requirements, assumptions, and key entities? [Consistency, Spec В§Clarifications, Spec В§FR-002, Spec В§Assumptions, Spec В§Key Entities]
+- [ ] CHK010 Are tie-handling requirements consistent between User Story 3, the edge-case section, FR-008, and SC-003? [Consistency, Spec В§User Story 3, Spec В§Edge Cases, Spec В§FR-008, Spec В§SC-003]
+- [ ] CHK011 Do the save-failure requirements align across User Story 3, FR-009, NFR-001, and SC-004 without implying contradictory partial-save behavior? [Consistency, Spec В§User Story 3, Spec В§FR-009, Spec В§SC-004]
+
+## Acceptance Criteria Quality
+
+- [ ] CHK012 Are the success criteria measurable without depending on hidden implementation details about the ranking engine? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec В§SC-001, Spec В§SC-003]
+- [ ] CHK013 Can reviewers objectively determine what qualifies as "used during later schedule ranking" from the written requirements alone? [Measurability, Spec В§User Story 1, Spec В§FR-007, Spec В§SC-001]
+- [ ] CHK014 Is the repeatability requirement for equal-priority ranking outcomes measurable enough to distinguish stable tie-breaking from accidental consistency? [Clarity, Spec В§SC-003]
+
+## Scenario Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK015 Are alternate-flow requirements defined for editing an existing saved priority set after the studentвЂ™s constraint list changes? [Coverage, Gap, Spec В§FR-012]
+- [ ] CHK016 Are recovery-flow requirements defined for what the student can do immediately after a save failure besides being told the previous priorities remain unchanged? [Coverage, Gap, Spec В§FR-009]
+- [ ] CHK017 Are requirements specified for switching between registration terms when both constraints and priority sets exist in multiple terms? [Coverage, Spec В§Edge Cases, Spec В§FR-011]
+
+## Edge Case Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK018 Are requirements explicit for mixed-validity submissions where one priority is missing and another is out of range in the same save attempt? [Edge Case, Gap, Spec В§FR-005, Spec В§FR-006]
+- [ ] CHK019 Are requirements defined for what happens when the editor display order changes after priorities were saved but before ranking is run? [Edge Case, Ambiguity, Spec В§FR-008]
+- [ ] CHK020 Are concurrent edit scenarios intentionally excluded or missing for the same student's priority set in multiple sessions? [Gap, Coverage]
+
