+## Scenario Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK018 Are primary, alternate, exception, and recovery scenarios all represented in the requirements for named set management? [Coverage, Spec В§User Scenarios & Testing]
+- [ ] CHK019 Are requirements defined for stale-session conflicts during rename, overwrite, and delete actions, not just save? [Coverage, Spec В§FR-013]
+- [ ] CHK020 Does the spec define what happens when a student attempts to rename a set using its own current normalized name? [Gap]
+
+## Edge Case Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK021 Are boundary conditions for naming, duplicate normalization, empty-state save attempts, and cross-term isolation all addressed in requirements? [Coverage, Spec В§Edge Cases]
+- [ ] CHK022 Are failure-handling requirements defined for each mutating action, including rename and delete, not only the initial save path? [Coverage, Spec В§FR-011]
+- [ ] CHK023 Are rollback expectations explicit when a mutating action fails after user confirmation? [Gap]
+
+## Non-Functional Requirements
+
+- [ ] CHK024 Are performance requirements quantified for all mutating actions and not just the initial save path? [Clarity, Spec В§NFR-001]
+- [ ] CHK025 Are plain-language messaging requirements specific enough to cover overwrite prompts, delete confirmations, invalid names, and stale-session refresh instructions? [Coverage, Spec В§NFR-002]
+- [ ] CHK026 Are keyboard-accessibility requirements defined for every saved-set management action and modal decision point? [Coverage, Spec В§NFR-003]
+- [ ] CHK027 Are privacy and ownership requirements explicit for viewing, listing, renaming, overwriting, deleting, and reusing saved sets? [Coverage, Spec В§NFR-004]
+
+## Dependencies & Assumptions
+
+- [ ] CHK028 Are assumptions about existing constraint-editing functionality and saved-set reuse behavior validated against the stated feature scope? [Assumption, Spec В§Assumptions]
+- [ ] CHK029 Are dependencies on profile storage and saved-set list reload behavior documented clearly enough to support acceptance validation? [Dependency, Spec В§Dependencies]
+
+## Ambiguities & Conflicts
+
