+# Compatibility Checklist: UC-29 Auto-pick Compatible Components
+
+**Purpose**: Validate the clarity, completeness, and consistency of requirements for compatibility-aware lecture, lab, tutorial, and shared-component schedule generation
+**Created**: 2026-03-11
+**Feature**: [spec.md](/home/thaia/ECE493Group19/specs/029-compatible-components/spec.md)
+
+**Note**: This checklist is generated by the `/speckit.checklist` command based on feature context and requirements.
+
+## Requirement Completeness
+
+- [ ] CHK001 Are requirements defined for how compatibility rules are retrieved before schedule generation begins? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-001]
+- [ ] CHK002 Are requirements explicit for courses with only some required component types, not only lecture/lab/tutorial triples? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-003]
+- [ ] CHK003 Are all major generation outcomes documented, including valid schedules, no-compatible-combination blocking, missing-rule blocking, shared-component handling, and generation failure? [Completeness, Spec В§FR-006]
+- [ ] CHK004 Does the spec define whether all valid compatible combinations should be considered or only a subset? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-005]
+- [ ] CHK005 Are cross-listed or shared-component scenarios explicitly included in the feature scope rather than implied only by edge cases? [Completeness, Spec В§US3]
+
+## Requirement Clarity
+
+- [ ] CHK006 Is вЂњcompatible component combinationвЂќ defined clearly enough to know what must be true before a schedule option is returned? [Clarity, Spec В§Key Entities]
+- [ ] CHK007 Is the policy for missing or inconsistent linkage rules unambiguous about whether generation is blocked or flagged? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-007]
+- [ ] CHK008 Is the rule for shared compatible components specific enough to prevent multiple reasonable display or counting interpretations? [Clarity, Spec В§FR-008]
+- [ ] CHK009 Is the phrase вЂњmakes the chosen compatible component pairings clearвЂќ quantified enough to be testable without interpretation drift? [Ambiguity, Spec В§FR-011]
+- [ ] CHK010 Is вЂњcurrent termвЂќ or вЂњselected termвЂќ used consistently enough to avoid ambiguity about the data scope of compatibility checks? [Consistency, Spec В§FR-001]
+
+## Requirement Consistency
+
+- [ ] CHK011 Do the user stories, edge cases, and functional requirements align on blocking generation when compatibility cannot be verified? [Consistency, Spec В§US2, Spec В§FR-007]
+- [ ] CHK012 Are the shared-component acceptance scenario and the shared-component functional requirement fully aligned on single representation and dual satisfaction semantics? [Consistency, Spec В§US3, Spec В§FR-008]
+- [ ] CHK013 Do the failure-handling requirements align between the use-case extension, user story 3, and `FR-009`? [Consistency, Spec В§US3, Spec В§FR-009]
+- [ ] CHK014 Are cross-term isolation requirements consistent between assumptions, dependencies, and `FR-010`? [Consistency, Spec В§FR-010]
+
+## Acceptance Criteria Quality
+
+- [ ] CHK015 Can each success criterion be objectively verified without inferring hidden scheduling behavior? [Measurability, Spec В§SC-001]
+- [ ] CHK016 Are the acceptance scenarios sufficient to distinguish вЂњno compatible combination existsвЂќ from вЂњcompatibility could not be verifiedвЂќ? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec В§US2]
+- [ ] CHK017 Is the shared-component success criterion measurable enough to detect both duplication and incorrect dual-satisfaction handling? [Measurability, Spec В§SC-004]
+
+## Scenario Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK018 Are primary, alternate, exception, and recovery-style outcomes represented across the user stories and requirements? [Coverage, Spec В§User Scenarios & Testing]
+- [ ] CHK019 Are requirements defined for mixed-course requests where one course blocks generation and others would otherwise be valid? [Coverage, Spec В§Edge Cases]
+- [ ] CHK020 Does the spec define how compatibility requirements apply when multiple courses each have several valid compatible combinations? [Coverage, Spec В§FR-005]
+
+## Edge Case Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK021 Are boundary conditions for missing component types, missing rules, contradictory rules, and shared components all addressed in the requirements? [Coverage, Spec В§Edge Cases]
+- [ ] CHK022 Are requirements explicit about returning no partial schedules after generation failure or unverifiable compatibility? [Coverage, Spec В§FR-007]
+- [ ] CHK023 Are rollback or consistency expectations defined when generation fails after some combinations have already been evaluated? [Gap]
+
+## Non-Functional Requirements
+
+- [ ] CHK024 Are performance requirements quantified for both successful generation and blocked-generation explanations? [Clarity, Spec В§NFR-001]
+- [ ] CHK025 Are plain-language messaging requirements specific enough to cover no-compatible-combination, missing-rule, shared-component, and failure outcomes? [Coverage, Spec В§NFR-002]
+- [ ] CHK026 Are privacy requirements explicit about using only the authenticated student's request and term context during generation? [Coverage, Spec В§NFR-003]
+- [ ] CHK027 Can the non-functional success target be measured consistently across success, block, and failure paths? [Measurability, Spec В§NFR-004]
+
+## Dependencies & Assumptions
+
+- [ ] CHK028 Are assumptions about catalog-provided linkage rules validated against the feature scope and edge cases? [Assumption, Spec В§Assumptions]
+- [ ] CHK029 Are dependencies on schedule-generator consumption of compatible combinations documented clearly enough to support downstream planning? [Dependency, Spec В§Dependencies]
+
+## Ambiguities & Conflicts
+
+- [ ] CHK030 Does the spec avoid ambiguous uses of вЂњcorrect,вЂќ вЂњcompatible,вЂќ and вЂњclearвЂќ unless operationally defined in context? [Ambiguity, Spec В§FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK031 Is the source of truth for compatibility linkage rules intentionally bounded, or is it still underspecified between catalog and timetable sources? [Gap, Spec В§Dependencies]
+
+## Notes
+
+- This checklist assumes standard reviewer depth for PR or spec review.
+- Focus areas selected: compatibility-rule completeness, blocked-generation policy, and shared-component clarity.
+- Actor/timing: reviewer during pre-implementation requirements review.
